# INDXR.AI — Cline Project Rules

## Project Context
YouTube transcript extraction SaaS. Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router, TypeScript), FastAPI (Python), Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth), Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Upstash Redis, Railway (backend), Vercel (frontend).

## Before Starting Any Task
- Read ARCHITECTURE.md, STATUS.md, and ROADMAP.md for full context
- Check STATUS.md for current priority order before proposing anything

## Design Rules
- Design system is defined in .cline/skills/indxr-design/ — use the indxr-design skill for all UI/styling work
- Never combine copy changes with design changes in one session
- Always support both Starlight (light mode) and Midnight (dark mode) in every component
- Prefer inline patterns over modals — modals cause information loss on dismiss

## Code Rules
- No band-aids — architectural fixes only, no timeouts or static workarounds
- Frontend uses NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY only — never the service role key
- Backend (FastAPI) uses SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY for admin actions only
- Credit mutations must go through the deduct_credits_atomic RPC — never direct DB writes

## Documentation
- Four core doc files only: ARCHITECTURE.md, STATUS.md, ROADMAP.md, DEVELOPMENT.md
- Update docs at the end of every session — AG handles this
- No new doc files without explicit reason
